@attribute [Route(AppStrings.Pages.About)]

<div style="max-width: 75ch">
    <header>
        <h1 class="display-6">Ready to Challenge Your Memory? Play Click & Match!</h1>
    </header>

    <section id="introduction">
        <p>Looking for a fun and brain-teasing game? Click & Match is here to put your memory to the test! Uncover matching pairs of tiles using as few clicks as possible. Simple rules, addictive gameplay, and increasing difficulty will keep you entertained for hours.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="how-to-play">
        <h2>How to Play:</h2>
        <ol>
            <li><b>Get Started:</b> Choose "Guest Play" or create your own profile to track your progress. (Include "Start Game" button with link)</li>
            <li><b>Level Up:</b> Begin with Level 1 and unlock higher levels (with more tiles) as you conquer them.</li>
            <li><b>Memory Boost:</b> Click on a tile to reveal its picture. Click another to see if it matches! (Optional: Add image or gif)</li>
            <li><b>Match Made:</b> If the tiles match, they'll disappear. If not, they'll flip back down. Remember their positions!</li>
            <li><b>Clear the Board:</b> Remove all tiles by finding their matches using the fewest clicks possible.</li>
            <li><b>Challenge Yourself:</b> Choose different themes with varying image sets, each offering a unique experience. (List available themes)</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section id="tips-tricks">
        <h2>Tips & Tricks:</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Pay close attention to revealed tiles and try to remember their locations.</li>
            <li>Start with smaller levels to get the hang of the game before tackling tougher ones.</li>
            <li>Some themes have fewer images, which means fewer levels. But don't worry, there are plenty to keep you busy!</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2024 Click & Match. All rights reserved.</p>
    </footer>
</div>